'''Laura Ruth Harrier''' (born March 28, 1990) is an American actress and former model. Harrier was first recognized for her portrayal of [[Destiny Evans]] in the short-lived reboot of the American [[soap opera]] ''[[One Life to Live]]'' (2013). She made her major film debut and breakthrough portraying [[Peter Parker]]'s love interest Liz in ''[[Spider-Man: Homecoming]]'' (2017).  

Harrier gained further recognition for portraying civil rights activist Patrice Dumas in ''[[BlacKkKlansman]]'' (2018), for which she received critical acclaim, and Camille Washington in the [[Netflix]] miniseries ''[[Hollywood (miniseries)|Hollywood]]'' (2020). 

==Early life==
Laura Ruth Harrier<ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=2014-02-19|title=Laura Ruth Harrier - Elite Model Management Chicago|url=http://i105.photobucket.com/albums/m240/SimplyLovely_the1st_2006/models3/1.jpg|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140219175715/http://i105.photobucket.com/albums/m240/SimplyLovely_the1st_2006/models3/1.jpg|archive-date=June 2, 2020|access-date=2020-06-02|website=[[Elite Model Management]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=2008|title=Laura Ruth Harrier - Wilhelmina Models|url=http://cdno-data.imagevenue.com/html.img146/upload2328/loc727/35384_2p_122_727lo.jpg|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200605220904/http://cdno-data.imagevenue.com/html.img146/upload2328/loc727/35384_2p_122_727lo.jpg|archive-date=June 5, 2020|access-date=June 5, 2020|website=[[Wilhelmina Models]]}}</ref> was born on March 28, 1990 in [[Chicago|Chicago, Illinois]], and was raised in [[Evanston, Illinois]].<ref name="ABCChicago">{{cite web|title=Laura Harrier, star of 'Spiderman: Homecoming' returns to Chicago|url=http://abc7chicago.com/entertainment/laura-harrier-star-of-spiderman-homecoming-returns-to-chicago/2127314/|date=June 21, 2017|publisher=[[WLS-TV]]|access-date=July 8, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170703111407/http://abc7chicago.com/entertainment/laura-harrier-star-of-spiderman-homecoming-returns-to-chicago/2127314/|archive-date=July 3, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="Elle">{{cite web|title=Everything You Need To Know About ‘Spider-Man’ Babe, Laura Harrier|url=http://www.elle.com.au/celebrity/laura-harrier-spiderman-facts-13641|author=Chang, Mahalia|date=July 3, 2017|work=[[Elle (magazine)|Elle]]|access-date=July 9, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170708075117/http://www.elle.com.au/celebrity/laura-harrier-spiderman-facts-13641|archive-date=July 8, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> She is biracial with a black father, Temujin Harrier, and a white mother, Linda (neé Sagan), of [[Poles|Polish]] and [[English people|English]] descent.<ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=2019-03-22|title=Laura Harrier|url=https://familytron.com/laura-harrier/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190531164104/https://familytron.com/laura-harrier/|archive-date=May 31, 2019|access-date=2020-06-15|website=Familytron|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Laura Harrier On Learning How To Take Care Of Her Hair|url=https://intothegloss.com/2018/08/laura-harrier-blackkklansman-hair-makeup-skincare-interview/|last=|first=|date=2018-08-09|website=Into The Gloss|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200411022703/https://intothegloss.com/2018/08/laura-harrier-blackkklansman-hair-makeup-skincare-interview/|archive-date=April 11, 2020|access-date=2020-05-04}}</ref><ref name=":1">{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=August 10, 2018|title=Laura Harrier|url=https://www.flaunt.com/content/laura-harrier|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200411025601/https://www.flaunt.com/content/laura-harrier|archive-date=April 11, 2020|access-date=2020-04-11|website=Flaunt Magazine|language=en-US}}</ref> Her father works in insurance and her mother is a speech pathologist.<ref name="Interview">{{cite web|author=Ortved, John|url=http://www.interviewmagazine.com/film/laura-harrier/|title=Laura Harrier|magazine=[[Interview (magazine)|Interview]]|date=June 14, 2016|access-date=June 27, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170625200850/http://www.interviewmagazine.com/film/laura-harrier|archive-date=June 25, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Laura Harrier: 'It's crazy people are surprised films with black people in do well'|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/go/london/film/laura-harrier-interview-balance-not-symmetry-spike-lee-a4201151.html|last=|first=|date=2019-07-30|website=[[Evening Standard]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200411032017/https://www.standard.co.uk/go/london/film/laura-harrier-interview-balance-not-symmetry-spike-lee-a4201151.html|archive-date=April 11, 2020|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref> She has one younger brother, William. She attended [[Evanston Township High School]] from 2004 to 2008.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Zwecker|first=Bill|date=2017-07-05|title=Evanston's Laura Harrier lands biggest role to date in 'Spider-Man'|url=https://chicago.suntimes.com/2017/7/5/18372970/evanston-s-laura-harrier-lands-biggest-role-to-date-in-spider-man|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191002092645/https://chicago.suntimes.com/2017/7/5/18372970/evanston-s-laura-harrier-lands-biggest-role-to-date-in-spider-man|archive-date=October 2, 2019|access-date=2020-04-27|website=[[Chicago Sun-Times]]|language=en}}</ref> She began modeling at the age of 17 after being discovered by her mother's friend, a [[Location scouting|location scout]].<ref name=":1" /><ref>{{Cite web|last=Bostedt|first=Shelbie Lynn|date=July 5, 2017|title='Spider-Man: Homecoming's' Laura Harrier is no damsel in distress|url=https://www.chicagotribune.com/redeye/ct-redeye-laura-harrier-interview-spiderman-homecoming-20170629-story.html|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200411051546/https://www.chicagotribune.com/redeye/ct-redeye-laura-harrier-interview-spiderman-homecoming-20170629-story.html|archive-date=April 11, 2020|access-date=2020-04-11|website=[[Chicago Tribune]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Lee|first=Jinnie|date=September 18, 2014|title=The Next Breakout Star You Need To Know Has Serious Style Game|url=https://www.refinery29.com/en-us/laura-harrier-ann-taylor-interview#slide-2|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191009131811/https://www.refinery29.com/en-us/laura-harrier-ann-taylor-interview#slide-2|archive-date=October 9, 2019|access-date=|website=[[Refinery29]]}}</ref>

After graduating high school, Harrier moved to [[New York City]] to study art<ref name=":1" /> at the [[New York University]] [[Gallatin School of Individualized Study]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=June 15, 2017|title=Laura Harrier Isn’t in Spider-Man: Homecoming Just to Look Pretty for Peter Parker|url=https://www.wmagazine.com/story/laura-harrier-spider-man-homecoming-feminist-mary-jane/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181004163847/https://www.wmagazine.com/story/laura-harrier-spider-man-homecoming-feminist-mary-jane|archive-date=October 4, 2018|access-date=2020-04-11|website=[[W (magazine)|W]]|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=|title=Laura Harrier's Style Icon is a 'Fresh Prince of Bel-Air' Character|url=https://www.instyle.com/celebrity/laura-harrier-interview|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180709220628/https://www.instyle.com/celebrity/laura-harrier-interview|archive-date=July 9, 2018|access-date=2020-06-05|website=[[InStyle Magazine]]|language=EN}}</ref> Upon arrival, Harrier initially deferred enrollment at the university but never attended the school nor graduated; she instead chose to continue modeling as she found herself booking profitable modeling work.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Lee|first=Jinnie|date=September 18, 2004|title=The Next Breakout Star You Need To Know Has Serious Style Game|url=https://www.refinery29.com/en-us/laura-harrier-ann-taylor-interview#slide-1|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191009131811/https://www.refinery29.com/en-us/laura-harrier-ann-taylor-interview#slide-1|archive-date=October 9, 2019|access-date=|website=[[Refinery29]]}}</ref> Eventually, she found that modeling was unfulfilling and decided to pursue acting after appearing in commercials and student films.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Balasundar|first=Gautam|date=2019-02-19|title=Laura Harrier Wants to Make Films She Never Saw Herself In|url=https://thelast-magazine.com/laura-harrier-blackkklansman-interview-profile/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200411031714/https://thelast-magazine.com/laura-harrier-blackkklansman-interview-profile/|archive-date=April 11, 2020|access-date=2020-04-18|website=The Last Magazine|language=en}}</ref><ref name=":2">{{Cite web|title=Tidal Magazine {{!}} Pretty in Pink|url=http://www.tidal-mag.com/magazine/pretty-in-pink|last=|first=|date=|website=Tidal Magazine|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200520153800/http://www.tidal-mag.com/magazine/pretty-in-pink|archive-date=May 20, 2020|access-date=2020-04-27}}</ref> She studied acting at the [[William Esper Studio]] from 2013 to 2015.<ref name=Interview/> After graduating she thought she'd be doing "weird, [[Off-Broadway|Off Broadway]] theater."<ref name="TheCut">{{cite web|author=Weatherford, Ashley|date=July 5, 2017|title=Laughing and Crying With Laura Harrier, the New Star of ''Spider-Man''|url=https://www.thecut.com/2017/07/laura-harrier-of-spider-man-homecoming-interviewed.html|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170811173043/https://www.thecut.com/2017/07/laura-harrier-of-spider-man-homecoming-interviewed.html|archive-date=August 11, 2017|access-date=July 5, 2017|publisher=[[New York (magazine)|The Cut]]}}</ref> 

==Career==

=== Acting ===
Harrier's first acting job was as main role [[Destiny Evans]] in the only season of the [[web series]] reboot of the American soap opera ''[[One Life to Live]]'' (2013). The role of Destiny was originated by actress Shenell Edmonds, who was offered the opportunity to reprise her role in the reboot but declined;<ref>{{Cite web|date=2013-02-22|title=Shenell Edmonds Declined 'One Life to Live' Reboot|url=https://www.soapoperanetwork.com/2013/02/shenell-edmonds-declined|access-date=2020-06-04|website=Soap Opera Network|language=en-US|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160422100456/http://www.soapoperanetwork.com/2013/02/shenell-edmonds-declined|archive-date=April 22, 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> Harrier took over the role after auditioning.<ref>{{Cite web|date=2013-07-03|title=Interview: One Life To Live’s Laura Harrier|url=https://soaps.sheknows.com/one-life-to-live/news/34013/interview-one-life-to-lives-laura-harrier/|access-date=2020-06-04|website=Soaps.com|language=en-US|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170613014840/http://soaps.sheknows.com/one-life-to-live/news/34013/interview-one-life-to-lives-laura-harrier|archive-date=June 13, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=2013-02-20|title=Exclusive! 'One Life to Live' Casts Its New Destiny|url=https://www.soapoperanetwork.com/2013/02/exclusive-one-life-to-live-casts-its-new-destiny|access-date=2020-06-04|website=Soap Opera Network|language=en-US|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161220200238/http://www.soapoperanetwork.com/2013/02/exclusive-one-life-to-live-casts-its-new-destiny|archive-date=December 20, 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> Her performance was generally praised with Errol Lewis from the [[Soap Opera Network|''Soap Opera Network'']] saying she "[has] nicely taken on the life of [her] [character]" and "the chemistry between [her and her on-screen boyfriend] is instantly there while leaving you wanting more."<ref>{{Cite web|last=Lewis|first=Errol|date=2013-04-26|title=Review: Breaking Down 'One Life to Live'|url=https://www.soapoperanetwork.com/2013/04/review-breaking-down-one-life-to-live|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170620005820/http://www.soapoperanetwork.com/2013/04/review-breaking-down-one-life-to-live|archive-date=June 20, 2017|access-date=2020-06-15|website=[[Soap Opera Network]]|language=en-US}}</ref>[[File:Laura Harrier by Gage Skidmore.jpg|left|thumb|upright|Harrier at the 2016 [[San Diego Comic-Con]] promoting ''Spider-Man: Homecoming''|alt=Actress Laura Harrier attending the 2015 San Diego Comic-Con International]]She next guest starred as Amber in the television series [[Unforgettable (American TV series)|''Unforgettable'']] (2014),<ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=|title=Unforgettable Episode Guide|url=http://www.iasfbo.inaf.it/~mauro/TV/PDF/ENDED/UNFORGET.pdf|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190403051839/http://www.iasfbo.inaf.it/~mauro/TV/PDF/ENDED/UNFORGET.pdf|archive-date=April 3, 2019|access-date=June 2, 2020|website=}}</ref> and made her film debut in [[The Last Five Years (film)|''The Last Five Years'']] (2014) as a woman who has an affair with Jamie, [[Jeremy Jordan (actor, born 1984)|Jeremy Jordan]]'s character.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Lee|first=Jinnie|date=|title=Actress Model Laura Harrier - Ann Taylor Fall 2014|url=https://www.refinery29.com/en-us/laura-harrier-ann-taylor-interview#slide-6|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191009131811/https://www.refinery29.com/en-us/laura-harrier-ann-taylor-interview#slide-6|archive-date=October 9, 2019|access-date=2020-06-04|website=[[Refinery29]]|language=en}}</ref> She was cast in the [[AMC (TV channel)|AMC]] pilot ''Galyntine'' (2014), opposite [[Alycia Debnam-Carey]], which was filmed but was not picked up and never aired.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.refinery29.com/en-us/laura-harrier-ann-taylor-interview#slide-7|title=The Next Breakout Star You Need To Know Has Serious Style Game|last=Lee|first=Jinnie|date=|website=[[Refinery29]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191009131811/https://www.refinery29.com/en-us/laura-harrier-ann-taylor-interview#slide-7|archive-date=October 9, 2019|access-date=2020-04-27}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.focusfeatures.com/blackkklansman/bio/laura-harrier|title=Laura Harrier Biography - BlacKkKlansman|last=|first=|date=|website=[[Focus Features]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191126040935/http://www.focusfeatures.com/blackkklansman/bio/laura-harrier|archive-date=November 26, 2019|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=|title=AMC Passes on Drama Pilots 'Knifeman,' 'Galyntine'|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/amc-passes-drama-pilots-knifeman-745408|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200411030912/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/amc-passes-drama-pilots-knifeman-745408|archive-date=April 11, 2020|access-date=2020-04-11|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|language=en}}</ref> In 2015, she appeared in the film ''[[4th Man Out]]'' <ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=|title='Fourth Man Out': Outfest Review|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/fourth-man-outfest-review-807617|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171202232915/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/fourth-man-outfest-review-807617|archive-date=December 2, 2017|access-date=2020-06-02|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|language=en}}</ref> and was cast in ''Codes of Conduct'', an [[HBO]] miniseries created by [[Steve McQueen (director)|Steve McQueen]]''.''<ref>{{Cite web|last=Kroll|first=Justin|date=2015-05-14|title=Laura Harrier Joins Steve McQueen’s ‘Codes of Conduct’|url=https://variety.com/2015/tv/news/laura-harrier-codes-of-conduct-cast-steve-mcqueen-1201496352/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200411022658/https://variety.com/2015/tv/news/laura-harrier-codes-of-conduct-cast-steve-mcqueen-1201496352/|archive-date=April 11, 2020|access-date=2020-04-11|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|language=en}}</ref> Harrier considers this pilot to be her first "real acting job".<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=|title=A Meeting with Laura Harrier|url=https://www.crash.fr/a-meeting-with-laura-harrier/|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-06-04|website=Crash Magazine}}</ref> The pilot was filmed but the series was canceled and never aired.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Chitwood|first=Adam|date=2018-10-26|title=Steve McQueen Says TV “Had Its Moment” & Gets Candid about His Cancelled HBO Series|url=https://collider.com/steve-mcqueen-tv-is-bad-hbo-netflix/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200411025601/https://collider.com/steve-mcqueen-tv-is-bad-hbo-netflix/|archive-date=April 11, 2020|access-date=2020-04-11|website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]]|language=en-US}}</ref>

In 2016, Harrier booked the role of [[Peter Parker]]'s love interest Liz, loosely based on [[Liz Allan]] from the comics, in ''[[Spider-Man: Homecoming]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Kroll|first=Justin|date=April 16, 2016|title=Tony Revolori and Laura Harrier Join 'Spider-Man: Homecoming'|url=https://variety.com/2016/film/news/tony-revolori-and-laura-harrier-join-spider-man-homecoming-1201754866/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200607010908/https://variety.com/2016/film/news/tony-revolori-and-laura-harrier-join-spider-man-homecoming-1201754866/|archive-date=June 6, 2020|access-date=December 15, 2017|website=|magazine=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Geier, Thom|first=|date=April 15, 2016|title='Spider-Man: Homecoming' Casts Laura Harrier From 'One Life to Live' (Exclusive)|url=https://www.thewrap.com/spider-man-homecoming-casts-laura-harrier-from-one-life-to-live-exclusive/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200607011146/https://www.thewrap.com/spider-man-homecoming-casts-laura-harrier-from-one-life-to-live-exclusive/#|archive-date=June 6, 2020|access-date=February 19, 2020|website=[[TheWrap]]|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Spider-Man Homecoming Characters Revealed|url=https://www.slashfilm.com/spider-man-homecoming-characters/|author=Anderson, Ethan|date=July 25, 2016|publisher=[[/Film]]|access-date=February 19, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190502140108/https://www.slashfilm.com/spider-man-homecoming-characters/|archive-date=May 2, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> After receiving an email from her agent about an audition for a [[Spider-Man]] project, she did two auditions and then a [[screen test]] with [[Tom Holland (actor)|Tom Holland]] before waiting six weeks to find out that she got the role.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Bostedt|first=Shelbie Lynn|date=|title='Spider-Man: Homecoming's' Laura Harrier is no damsel in distress|url=https://www.chicagotribune.com/redeye/ct-redeye-laura-harrier-interview-spiderman-homecoming-20170629-story.html|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200411051546/https://www.chicagotribune.com/redeye/ct-redeye-laura-harrier-interview-spiderman-homecoming-20170629-story.html|archive-date=April 11, 2020|access-date=2020-06-04|website=[[Chicago Tribune]]}}</ref> The film was released in July 2017, marking Harrier's major film debut and breakthrough, and was a box office success, grossing over $880 million worldwide and received generally positive reviews.<ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=|title=Spider-Man: Homecoming - Rotten Tomatoes|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/spider_man_homecoming|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170708205041/https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/spider_man_homecoming|archive-date=July 8, 2017|access-date=June 15, 2020|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=|title=Spider-Man: Homecoming|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/release/rl863208961/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200609095044/https://www.boxofficemojo.com/release/rl863208961/|archive-date=June 9, 2020|access-date=2020-06-15|website=[[Box Office Mojo]]}}</ref> While the film brought Harrier substantial fame and established her as an actress,<ref>{{Cite web|last=Seth|first=Radhika|date=6 May 2019|title=Laura Harrier Unveils A Dramatic New Look At The Met Gala|url=https://www.vogue.co.uk/article/laura-harrier-2019-met-gala-look|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200615132226/https://www.vogue.co.uk/article/laura-harrier-2019-met-gala-look|archive-date=June 15, 2020|access-date=2020-06-15|website=[[British Vogue]]|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=de Pressigny|first=Clementine|date=2018-05-08|title=this is the story of laura harrier, who is going to make hollywood her town|url=https://i-d.vice.com/en_us/article/ne9887/this-is-laura-harrier-spider-man-black-klansman|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200615132230/https://i-d.vice.com/en_us/article/ne9887/this-is-laura-harrier-spider-man-black-klansman|archive-date=June 15, 2020|access-date=2020-06-15|website=[[i-D]]|language=en}}</ref> her performance was met with mixed reviews with critics disappointed in her character's development and lack of screen time.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Deino|first=Daryl|date=2017-07-14|title=‘Spider-Man: Homecoming’ Doesn’t Measure Up to 2004’s Masterpiece|url=https://observer.com/2017/07/spider-man-homecoming-review/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302001411/https://observer.com/2017/07/spider-man-homecoming-review/|archive-date=March 2, 2020|access-date=2020-06-15|website=[[The New York Observer|Observer]]|language=en-US}}</ref> [[Dana Schwartz]] of ''[[Marie Claire]]'' gave a negative review: "Liz is always reactionary; she doesn't ''do'' anything in this movie because she doesn't have to—she's simply the pretty face that Peter cares about and wants to impress. She drives the plot forward the same way any film prop might—an [[Infinity Stone|infinity stone]], or enchanted spear, or what have you. Liz could literally be replaced by an object and the beats of the movie wouldn't change at all."<ref>{{Cite web|last=Schwartz|first=Dana|date=2017-07-07|title='Spider-Man: Homecoming' Is a Wonderfully Written Movie with Woefully Written Women|url=https://www.marieclaire.com/culture/news/a28090/spider-man-homecoming-review/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190621052203/https://www.marieclaire.com/culture/news/a28090/spider-man-homecoming-review/|archive-date=June 21, 2019|access-date=2020-06-15|website=[[Marie Claire]]|language=en-US}}</ref> Her performance was praised by several critics for avoiding the [[damsel in distress]] trope, with Jim Vejvoda from ''[[IGN]]'' saying "Harrier nicely plays against expectations,"<ref>{{Cite web|last=Vejvoda|first=Jim|date=29 Jun 2017|title=Spider-Man: Homecoming Review|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2017/06/29/spider-man-homecoming-review|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200615124209/https://www.ign.com/articles/2017/06/29/spider-man-homecoming-review|archive-date=June 15, 2020|access-date=June 15, 2020|website=[[IGN]]}}</ref> and Mark Hughes wrote for ''[[Forbes]]'' that Harrier "is a welcome change to the usual romantic interests in superhero films" and "makes Liz into a likable, sympathetic, [[Type A and Type B personality theory|type-A]] person."<ref>{{Cite web|last=Hughes|first=Mark|date=Jul 5, 2017|title=Review: 'Spider-Man Homecoming' Is A Series-Best Destined To Be Fan-Favorite|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/markhughes/2017/07/05/review-spider-man-homecoming-is-a-series-best-destined-to-be-fan-favorite/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200615124209/https://www.forbes.com/sites/markhughes/2017/07/05/review-spider-man-homecoming-is-a-series-best-destined-to-be-fan-favorite/|archive-date=June 15, 2020|access-date=2020-06-15|website=[[Forbes]]|language=en}}</ref>  

[[File:Laura Harrier Cannes 2018.jpg|thumb|upright|Harrier at the 2018 [[Cannes Film Festival]] for ''BlacKkKlansman''|alt=Side profile of Laura Harrier at the 2018 Cannes Film Festival]]

In June 2017, it was announced that Harrier would be portraying Millie Montag in ''[[Fahrenheit 451 (2018 film)|Fahrenheit 451]]'', HBO's film adaptation of the acclaimed [[Fahrenheit 451|novel of the same name]], opposite [[Michael B. Jordan]];<ref name="F451_1">{{cite web|author=Petski, Denise|first=|date=June 2017|title='Fahrenheit 451': Laura Harrier Cast As Millie In HBO Movie|url=https://deadline.com/2017/06/fahrenheit-451-laura-harrier-cast-millie-hbo-movie-1202120406/amp/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190502140053/https://deadline.com/2017/06/fahrenheit-451-laura-harrier-cast-millie-hbo-movie-1202120406/amp/|archive-date=May 2, 2019|access-date=February 19, 2020|website=[[Deadline Hollywood|Deadline]]}}</ref> however, her part was later cut by the director who decided the character did not fit with the storyline and wanted to shorten the film's runtime.<ref name="F451_2">{{cite web|last=Pond|first=Steve|date=May 9, 2018|title=‘BlacKkKlansman’ Star Laura Harrier on Going From Spider-Man’s Homecoming to Cannes Red Carpet|url=https://www.thewrap.com/blackkklansman-star-laura-harrier-going-spider-mans-homecoming-cannes-red-carpet/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180527093011/https://www.thewrap.com/blackkklansman-star-laura-harrier-going-spider-mans-homecoming-cannes-red-carpet/|archive-date=May 27, 2018|accessdate=May 30, 2018|website=[[TheWrap]]}}</ref> Harrier co-starred as Patrice Dumas, a civil rights activist, in the film ''[[BlacKkKlansman]]'' (2018) opposite [[John David Washington]], [[Adam Driver]], and [[Topher Grace]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=D'Alessandro|first1=Anthony|date=25 October 2017|title=Adam Driver Joins Spike Lee’s ‘Black Klansman’|url=https://deadline.com/2017/10/adam-driver-spike-lee-black-klansman-1202194537/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190502140112/https://deadline.com/2017/10/adam-driver-spike-lee-black-klansman-1202194537/|archive-date=May 2, 2019|accessdate=18 May 2018|website=[[Deadline Hollywood|Deadline]]}}</ref> The director, [[Spike Lee]], handpicked Harrier after seeing an audition tape she had done for another project.<ref name=":2" /> She was on vacation in [[Greece]] when Lee demanded that she meet him in New York City for an audition, where he acted as her scene partner.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Smith|first=Krista|date=|title=Laura Harrier Doesn’t Blame Spike Lee for Interrupting Her Vacation|url=https://www.vanityfair.com/style/2018/08/laura-harrier-blackkklansman-actress|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-06-04|website=[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]]|language=en}}</ref> The next day, she was offered the role. In preparation for it, Harrier met with activist [[Kathleen Cleaver]] and other women who were in the [[Black Power movement]], studied [[Angela Davis]], and contacted people who were in the Black Student Union at [[Colorado College]] during the 1970s.<ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=|title=CC Featured in Upcoming Spike Lee Film • Colorado College|url=https://www.coloradocollege.edu/newsevents/newsroom/cc-featured-in-upcoming-spike-lee-film#.Xtipbp5Kh_Q|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180524045209/https://www.coloradocollege.edu/newsevents/newsroom/cc-featured-in-upcoming-spike-lee-film#.Xtipbp5Kh_Q|archive-date=May 24, 2018|access-date=2020-06-04|website=[[Colorado College]]|language=en}}</ref><ref name=":5">{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=|title=Hunger 15 cover star Laura Harrier on Spike Lee and Hollywood's new era|url=https://www.hungertv.com/editorial/hunger-15-cover-star-laura-harrier-on-spike-lee-and-hollywoods-new-era/|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-06-04|website=Hunger|language=en-US}}</ref> All of these people were Harrier's inspirations and influences for the role.<ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=2018-08-09|title=Q&A: Don't ask 'BlacKkKlansman' actress Laura Harrier about being a black woman in Hollywood|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/movies/la-et-mn-laura-harrier-blackkklansman-20180809-story.html|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191230185112/https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/movies/la-et-mn-laura-harrier-blackkklansman-20180809-story.html|archive-date=December 30, 2019|access-date=2020-06-04|website=[[Los Angeles Times]]|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Marinelli|first=Gina|title=Laura Harrier's BlacKkKlansman Role Breaks More Than One Stereotype|url=https://www.whowhatwear.com/laura-harrier-blackkklansman-interview|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190816051608/https://www.whowhatwear.com/laura-harrier-blackkklansman-interview|archive-date=August 16, 2019|access-date=2020-06-04|website=Who What Wear|language=en}}</ref> Harrier also attended several of Lee's classes at New York University where he is a film professor.<ref>{{Cite web|date=2019-08-17|title=Actress Laura Harrier talks film icons, fashion and fulfilling her romcom dream|url=https://www.marieclaire.co.uk/entertainment/tv-and-film/laura-harrier-663290|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200524054734/https://www.marieclaire.co.uk/entertainment/tv-and-film/laura-harrier-663290|archive-date=May 24, 2020|access-date=2020-06-04|website=[[Marie Claire]]|language=en}}</ref> For her performance, Harrier received critical acclaim and was nominated for a [[Black Reel Award for Outstanding Breakthrough Performance, Female|Black Reel Award]]<ref name=":3" /> and a [[Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by a Cast in a Motion Picture|Screen Actors Guild Award]].<ref name=":4" />

In 2019, director Jamie Adams offered Harrier the lead role in his film [[Balance, Not Symmetry|''Balance, Not Symmetry'']]; she accepted the role due to the project being [[improvised]] and being good friends with [[Bria Vinaite]], her co-star in the film.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Potier|first=Laura|date=2019-07-31|title=Laura Harrier and Bria Vinaite discuss Balance, Not Symmetry and filmmaking as activism|url=http://outtakemag.co.uk/interviews/2019/07/31/laura-harrier-bria-vinaite-biffy-clyro/|access-date=2020-06-04|website=Outtake Magazine|language=en-GB}}</ref> She plays Caitlyn Walker, an art student at the [[Glasgow School of Art]], who is struggling with the recent death of her father. The project was a critical failure.<ref>{{cite web|last=Grater|first=Tom|date=October 5, 2018|title=Laura Harrier, Bria Vinaite, Lily Newmark board 'Balance, Not Symmetry' with Biffy Clyro (exclusive)|url=https://www.screendaily.com/news/laura-harrier-bria-vinaite-lily-newmark-board-balance-not-symmetry-with-biffy-clyro-exclusive/5133310.article|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181231043044/https://www.screendaily.com/news/laura-harrier-bria-vinaite-lily-newmark-board-balance-not-symmetry-with-biffy-clyro-exclusive/5133310.article|archive-date=December 31, 2018|accessdate=December 30, 2018|website=Screen International}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=|title=Balance, Not Symmetry - Rotten Tomatoes|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/balance_not_symmetry|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=June 14, 2020|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]}}</ref> Cath Clarke of ''[[The Guardian]]'' thought Harrier gave a "blank performance."<ref>{{Cite news|last=Clarke|first=Cath|date=2019-08-01|title=Balance, Not Symmetry review – Biffy Clyro art-school drama topples into cliche|language=en-GB|work=[[The Guardian]]|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2019/aug/01/balance-not-symmetry-review-biffy-clyro-art-school-bria-vinaite-simon-neil|url-status=live|access-date=2020-04-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200411011535/https://www.theguardian.com/film/2019/aug/01/balance-not-symmetry-review-biffy-clyro-art-school-bria-vinaite-simon-neil|archive-date=April 11, 2020|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> 

She starred in the [[Netflix]] miniseries ''[[Hollywood (miniseries)|Hollywood]]'' (2020) by [[Ryan Murphy (writer)|Ryan Murphy]] as Camille Washington, an up-and-coming black actress facing prejudice during the [[Hollywood Golden Age]] in the post-[[World War II]] era.<ref>{{Cite web|last1=Petski|first1=Denise|last2=Andreeva|first2=Nellie|date=2019-09-27|title=‘Hollywood’: Dylan McDermott, Samara Weaving, Jim Parsons, Maude Apatow & Joe Mantello Among Netflix Series Cast Additions|url=https://deadline.com/2019/09/dylan-mcdermott-samara-weaving-jim-parsons-maude-apatow-joe-mantello-ryan-murphy-netflix-series-hollywood-1202746400/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200524021658/https://deadline.com/2019/09/dylan-mcdermott-samara-weaving-jim-parsons-maude-apatow-joe-mantello-ryan-murphy-netflix-series-hollywood-1202746400/|archive-date=May 24, 2020|access-date=2020-04-11|website=[[Deadline Hollywood|Deadline]]|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Miller|first=Julie|date=|title=Inside Ryan Murphy’s Hollywood, a Revisionist Homage to Golden Age Tinseltown|url=https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2020/04/inside-ryan-murphys-hollywood-a-revisionist-homage-to-golden-age-tinseltown|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-11|website=[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]]|language=en}}</ref> Prior to booking her role, all Harrier knew was that it was an untitled Old Hollywood project. She had an initial audition where she read for the part and then months later was called in once more to do a chemistry read for Ryan Murphy with her on-screen boyfriend [[Darren Criss]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=Gonzales|first=Erica|date=2020-05-11|title=Laura Harrier Feels Seen|url=https://www.harpersbazaar.com/culture/film-tv/a32397715/laura-harrier-interview/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200526090950/https://www.harpersbazaar.com/culture/film-tv/a32397715/laura-harrier-interview/|archive-date=May 26, 2020|access-date=2020-06-04|website=[[Harper's Bazaar]]|language=en-US}}</ref> Harrier largely drew inspiration for the role from actress [[Dorothy Dandridge]] due to her having faced similar struggles as Camille does in the series.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Frederick|first=Candice|date=2020-05-07|title=Laura Harrier on Rewriting Hollywood in Netflix’s ‘Hollywood’|language=en-US|work=[[The New York Times]]|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/05/07/arts/television/hollywood-laura-harrier-netflix.html|url-status=live|access-date=2020-06-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200508173742/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/05/07/arts/television/hollywood-laura-harrier-netflix.html|archive-date=May 8, 2020|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> Harrier was also inspired somewhat by singer and actress [[Lena Horne]]. Both Dandridge and Camille were nominated for the [[Academy Award for Best Actress]] but it was Camille who won the Oscar. In preparation for her character's speech, Harrier studied and was influenced by [[Halle Berry]]'s 2002 Oscars acceptance speech for the same award.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Laura Harrier on Studying Dorothy Dandridge, Halle Berry to Play a Star on the Rise in Netflix’s ‘Hollywood’|url=https://variety.com/2020/tv/news/laura-harrier-hollywood-netflix-interview-ryan-murphy-dorothy-dandridge-halle-berry-1234592690/|last=Jackson|first=Angelique|date=2020-05-04|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200506053715/https://variety.com/2020/tv/news/laura-harrier-hollywood-netflix-interview-ryan-murphy-dorothy-dandridge-halle-berry-1234592690/|archive-date=May 6, 2020|access-date=2020-05-06}}</ref><ref name=":9" /> The series and Harrier's performance received mixed reviews,<ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=|title=Hollywood - Rotten Tomatoes|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/hollywood/s01|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=June 15, 2020|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=James|first=Kendra|date=2020-05-02|title=Ryan Murphy’s new Netflix show tries to fix Hollywood’s history|url=https://www.polygon.com/2020/5/2/21244163/ryan-murphy-hollywood-review-netflix-darren-criss-michelle-krusiec-pose|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200511233547/https://www.polygon.com/2020/5/2/21244163/ryan-murphy-hollywood-review-netflix-darren-criss-michelle-krusiec-pose|archive-date=May 11, 2020|access-date=2020-06-15|website=[[Polygon]]|language=en}}</ref> with some critics comparing her performance unfavorably to her work in ''BlacKkKlansmman''.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Snow|first=Philippa|date=2020-05-01|title=Hollywood Keeps Trying to Rewrite Its History|work=[[The New Republic]]|url=https://newrepublic.com/article/157534/hollywood-keeps-trying-rewrite-history-netflix-ryan-murphy-review|url-status=live|access-date=2020-06-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200510192217/https://newrepublic.com/article/157534/hollywood-keeps-trying-rewrite-history-netflix-ryan-murphy-review|archive-date=May 10, 2020|issn=0028-6583}}</ref> [[The Hollywood Reporter|''The Hollywood Reporter'']]'s Daniel Fienberg noted she "looks the part" but Camille is undeveloped."<ref>{{Cite web|last=Fienberg|first=Daniel|date=April 29, 2020|title='Hollywood': TV Review|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/hollywood-review-1292304|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200510183917/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/hollywood-review-1292304|archive-date=May 10, 2020|access-date=2020-06-15|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|language=en}}</ref> Darren Franich and Kristen Baldwin from ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' thought she was "so charismatic in ''BlackkKlansman'' [...] but there’s no sign of that fire here."<ref>{{Cite web|last=Franich|first=Darren|last2=Baldwin|first2=Kristen|date=April 29, 2020|title='Hollywood' review: Ryan Murphy's showbiz dramedy splits EW's critics|url=https://ew.com/tv/tv-reviews/hollywood-review-netflix-ryan-murphy/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200515053718/https://ew.com/tv/tv-reviews/hollywood-review-netflix-ryan-murphy/|archive-date=May 15, 2020|access-date=2020-06-15|website=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|language=EN}}</ref> There were positive reviews including Gabriel Tate from the [[I (newspaper)|''i'' newspaper]] who called her "heartbreakingly convincing."<ref>{{Cite web|last=Tate|first=Gabriel|date=2020-05-01|title=Hollywood is corny, bland and brusque — what happened to Ryan Murphy?|url=https://inews.co.uk/culture/hollywood-netflix-review-ryan-murphy-423903|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-06-15|website=[[i (newspaper)|i]]|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Pham|first=Jason|date=2020-05-01|title=Like Her Character, Laura Harrier Is the Breakout Star of ‘Hollywood’|url=https://stylecaster.com/hollywood-netflix-review/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200609052218/https://stylecaster.com/hollywood-netflix-review/|archive-date=June 9, 2020|access-date=2020-06-15|website=[[StyleCaster]]|language=en}}</ref> 

Harrier will next star in [[Bios (film)|''Bios'']] with [[Tom Hanks]],<ref name=":6">{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=September 6, 2019|title=Laura Harrier Is Just Getting Started|url=https://www.wmagazine.com/story/laura-harrier-cover-interview-fios-hollywood/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191103104205/https://www.wmagazine.com/story/laura-harrier-cover-interview-fios-hollywood|archive-date=November 3, 2019|access-date=2020-04-30|website=[[W (magazine)|W]]|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=May 22, 2019|title=Skeet Ulrich and Laura Harrier Join Tom Hank's Sci-Fi Film Bios|url=https://www.comingsoon.net/movies/news/1070099-skeet-ulrich-and-laura-harrier-join-bios|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200607011547/https://www.comingsoon.net/movies/news/1070099-skeet-ulrich-and-laura-harrier-join-bios|archive-date=June 6, 2020|access-date=2020-04-30|website=ComingSoon|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Arnaud|first=Henry|date=May 8, 2020|title=Laura Harrier: La Decouverte De Hollywood|url=https://www.goldenglobes.com/articles/laura-harrier-la-decouverte-de-hollywood|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200613021832/https://www.goldenglobes.com/articles/laura-harrier-la-decouverte-de-hollywood|archive-date=June 13, 2020|access-date=2020-06-13|website=[[Golden Globe Awards]]|language=fr}}</ref> which is set to premiere on April 16, 2021,<ref>{{cite web|last=D'Alessandro|first=Anthony|date=June 12, 2020|title=Tom Hanks Sci-Fi Movie ‘Bios’ Moves To 2021|url=https://deadline.com/2020/06/tom-hanks-sci-fi-movie-bios-moves-to-2021-1202958422/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200613004915/https://deadline.com/2020/06/tom-hanks-sci-fi-movie-bios-moves-to-2021-1202958422/|archive-date=June 13, 2020|accessdate=June 12, 2020|website=[[Deadline Hollywood|Deadline]]}}</ref> and in ''[[The Starling]]'' alongside [[Melissa McCarthy]], which is set to premiere on Netflix.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Netflix Wins Rights to Ted Melfi's 'The Starling' With Melissa McCarthy and Kevin Kline|url=https://www.thewrap.com/netflix-wins-rights-to-ted-melfis-the-starling-with-melissa-mccarthy-and-kevin-kline/|last=|first=|date=2020-04-20|website=[[TheWrap]]|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200429030138/https://www.thewrap.com/netflix-wins-rights-to-ted-melfis-the-starling-with-melissa-mccarthy-and-kevin-kline/|archive-date=April 29, 2020|access-date=2020-04-30}}</ref>

===Modeling and fashion===
Harrier starred alongside [[Rowan Blanchard]] and [[Mahershala Ali]] in ''The Realest Real'' (2016) directed by [[Carrie Brownstein]], a campaign film for luxury French fashion brand [[Kenzo (brand)|Kenzo]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kenzo.com/eu/en/thereal|title=The Realest Real - Autumn Winter 2016 Collection {{!}} KENZO|last=|first=|date=|website=[[Kenzo (brand) | Kenzo]]|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191122152852/https://www.kenzo.com/eu/en/thereal|archive-date=November 22, 2019|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vogue.com/article/kenzo-premiere-the-realest-real-2|title=Kenzo Premieres Their Latest Campaign Film, The Realest Real|last=Simpson|first=Ashley W.|date=|website=[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190628112721/https://www.vogue.com/article/kenzo-premiere-the-realest-real-2|archive-date=June 28, 2019|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref> Harrier has modeled for campaigns with companies such as [[Urban Outfitters]], [[American Eagle Outfitters|American Eagle]], [[Target Corporation|Target]], [[Aldo Group|ALDO]], [[Steve Madden (company)|Steve Madden]], and [[L'Oréal]]. Harrier has also been part of [[Calvin Klein (company)|Calvin Klein]]<ref>{{Cite web|last=Fisher|first=Lauren Alexis|date=2017-04-18|title=Lauren Hutton, 73, Stars in Calvin Klein's New Underwear Campaign|url=https://www.harpersbazaar.com/fashion/designers/news/a22061/calvin-klein-womens-underwear-campaign-spring-2017/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200506051325/https://www.harpersbazaar.com/fashion/designers/news/a22061/calvin-klein-womens-underwear-campaign-spring-2017/|archive-date=May 6, 2020|access-date=2020-04-18|website=[[Harper's Bazaar]]|language=en-US}}</ref> and [[Louis Vuitton]] campaigns.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Penrose|first=Nerisha|date=2019-01-14|title=Louis Vuitton's Latest Campaign is Stacked With Hollywood Stars|url=https://www.elle.com/fashion/trend-reports/a25891743/louis-vuitton-hollywood-stars-pre-fall-2019-campaign/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190207233605/https://www.elle.com/fashion/trend-reports/a25891743/louis-vuitton-hollywood-stars-pre-fall-2019-campaign/|archive-date=February 7, 2019|access-date=2020-04-18|website=[[Elle (magazine)|Elle]]|language=en-US}}</ref> She is an ambassador for the latter and for luxury Italian jewelry brand [[Bvlgari]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bulgari.com/en-us/magazine/jon-kortajarena-the-new-bulgari-global-watches-ambassador|title=Basel World|publisher=[[Bulgari]]|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170807235801/https://www.bulgari.com/en-us/magazine/jon-kortajarena-the-new-bulgari-global-watches-ambassador|archive-date=August 7, 2017|accessdate=July 9, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=|title=Oscars 2019: Laura Harrier Explains How Her Sustainable Louis Vuitton Dress Was Made|url=https://www.wmagazine.com/story/oscars-2019-laura-harrier-louis-vuitton-behind-the-scenes/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191112034132/https://www.wmagazine.com/story/oscars-2019-laura-harrier-louis-vuitton-behind-the-scenes|archive-date=November 12, 2019|access-date=2020-04-18|website=[[W (magazine)|W]]|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nypost.com/2020/01/24/emma-roberts-sophie-turner-and-more-embrace-their-inner-geeks-for-louis-vuitton/|title=Emma Roberts, Sophie Turner and more embrace their inner geeks for Louis Vuitton|last=Masters|first=Johannah|date=2020-01-24|website=[[New York Post]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200405043055/https://nypost.com/2020/01/24/emma-roberts-sophie-turner-and-more-embrace-their-inner-geeks-for-louis-vuitton/|archive-date=April 5, 2020|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref> She has appeared in magazines such as ''[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]'', ''[[Cosmopolitan (magazine)|Cosmopolitan]]'', ''[[Elle (magazine)|Elle]]'', and ''[[Glamour (magazine)|Glamour]]''.<ref name="Elle" /><ref name="TheCut" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.byrdie.com/laura-harrier-acne-treatments|title=The 5 Products Actress Laura Harrier Swears By to Fight Acne|last=Bowen|first=Alyss|website=Byrdie|language=en|access-date=2020-04-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200411022658/https://www.byrdie.com/laura-harrier-acne-treatments|archive-date=April 11, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=|title=Aldo Shoes S/S 16 (Aldo)|url=https://models.com/work/aldo-shoes-aldo-shoes-ss-16|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200411043909/https://models.com/work/aldo-shoes-aldo-shoes-ss-16|archive-date=April 11, 2020|access-date=2020-04-11|website=Models.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=|title=Aerie|url=https://worktablenyc.com/aerie|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200610171737/https://worktablenyc.com/aerie|archive-date=June 10, 2020|access-date=2020-06-10|website=Worktable|language=en-US}}</ref>

==Personal life==
After graduating high school, Harrier moved to New York City in 2008,<ref name="Interview" /> relocating to [[Los Angeles]] in 2019;<ref name=":2" /><ref name=":6" /> she has said that she made the move to Los Angeles to advance her career.<ref name=":9">{{Cite web|last=Bell|first=Crystal|date=|title=Laura Harrier Is The Hollywood Star With A New York State Of Mind|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/3165999/laura-harrier-hollywood-interview/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200528113123/http://www.mtv.com/news/3165999/laura-harrier-hollywood-interview/|archive-date=May 28, 2020|access-date=2020-06-04|website=[[MTV News]]|language=en}}</ref> Harrier is also an avid patron of the arts and exhibitions and collects art, which she decorates her home with.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Vadnal|first=Julie|date=|title=Laura Harrier Doesn’t Care What You Think About Her Light Pink L.A. Home|url=https://www.architecturaldigest.com/story/laura-harrier-doesnt-care-what-you-think-about-her-light-pink-la-home|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200526003435/https://www.architecturaldigest.com/story/laura-harrier-doesnt-care-what-you-think-about-her-light-pink-la-home|archive-date=May 26, 2020|access-date=2020-06-04|website=[[Architectural Digest]]|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=2020-04-17|title=Cultured Young Collectors 2020|url=https://www.culturedmag.com/cultured-young-collectors-2020/|access-date=2020-06-04|website=Cultured Magazine|language=en-US|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200510233419/https://www.culturedmag.com/cultured-young-collectors-2020/|archive-date=May 10, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Binlot|first=Ann|date=|title=Tessa Thompson and Laura Harrier Bring Hollywood to Art Basel|url=https://www.vanityfair.com/style/2018/12/art-basel-tessa-thompson-laura-harrier|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-06-04|website=[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]]|language=en}}</ref>

Harrier is a passionate supporter of [[Civil and political rights|civil rights]] and advocates for issues such as [[intersectional feminism]],<ref name=":5" /> [[transgender rights]], [[gun control]], [[gender equality]], and [[Representation of African Americans in media|representation]] for both black people and people of color in general.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Liebman|first=Lisa|date=2018-08-13|title=Laura Harrier on Her ‘Nerve-racking’ Performance In BlacKkKlansman|url=https://www.vulture.com/2018/08/laura-harrier-on-the-nerve-wracking-blackkklansman.html|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200524054401/https://www.vulture.com/2018/08/laura-harrier-on-the-nerve-wracking-blackkklansman.html|archive-date=May 24, 2020|access-date=2020-06-04|website=Vulture|language=en-us}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Dodson|first=P. Claire|date=|title=Logan Browning Says Women of Color in Hollywood "Deserve More Than Good Enough"|url=https://www.teenvogue.com/story/dear-white-people-orange-is-the-new-black-actors-talk-representation-in-hollywood|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-06-04|website=[[Teen Vogue]]|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Cerón|first=Ella|date=|title=Laura Harrier Hopes Hollywood Looks Completely Different in 10 Years|url=https://www.teenvogue.com/story/laura-harrier-young-hollywood-2018|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190617160054/https://www.teenvogue.com/story/laura-harrier-young-hollywood-2018|archive-date=June 17, 2019|access-date=2020-06-04|website=[[Teen Vogue]]|language=en}}</ref> She frequently uses her [[Instagram]] to call out injustices and has voiced support for [[Planned Parenthood]] and the [[American Civil Liberties Union]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=Mahanty|first=Shannon|date=May 19, 2017|title=World, Meet Laura Harrier|url=https://www.asos.com/women/fashion-feed/2017_05_19-fri/laura-harrier-asos-magazine/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180207142359/http://www.asos.com/women/fashion-feed/2017_05_19-fri/laura-harrier-asos-magazine/|archive-date=February 7, 2018|access-date=|website=[[ASOS (retailer)|ASOS]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=2017-11-14|title=Exclusive: Semaine’s New Trump Film Is the Ultimate Resistance Piece|url=https://coveteur.com/2017/11/14/semaine-new-film-the-emperor-donald-trump/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191003103925/http://coveteur.com/2017/11/14/semaine-new-film-the-emperor-donald-trump/|archive-date=October 3, 2019|access-date=2020-06-04|website=Coveteur}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=August 2, 2018|title=New Video from Planned Parenthood feat. Sia’s Unstoppable Brings to Life the Unstoppable Manifesto|url=https://www.plannedparenthood.org/about-us/newsroom/press-releases/new-video-from-planned-parenthood-feat-sias-unstoppable-brings-to-life-the-unstoppable-manifesto|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181120074120/https://www.plannedparenthood.org/about-us/newsroom/press-releases/new-video-from-planned-parenthood-feat-sias-unstoppable-brings-to-life-the-unstoppable-manifesto|archive-date=November 20, 2018|access-date=2020-06-04|website=[[Planned Parenthood]]|language=en}}</ref> She was also one of the celebrity signatories for the [[Time's Up (movement)|Time's Up movement]],<ref name=":2" /><ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=2019-10-21|title=The 300+ Original Time's Up Signatories|url=https://timesupnow.org/times-up-the-300-original-signatories/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200503222948/https://timesupnow.org/times-up-the-300-original-signatories/|archive-date=May 3, 2020|access-date=2020-06-04|website=[[Time's Up (movement)|Time's Up Now]]|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Ogunnaike|first=Nikki|date=2018-03-28|title=Laura Harrier Is Ready to Be the Next James Bond|url=https://www.elle.com/fashion/a19599053/laura-harrier-louis-vuitton-profile/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190213003938/https://www.elle.com/fashion/a19599053/laura-harrier-louis-vuitton-profile/|archive-date=February 13, 2019|access-date=2020-06-04|website=[[Elle (magazine)|Elle]]|language=en-US}}</ref> and donated $1,000 to support the cause.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Magazine|first=The Fashion Plate|date=2018-01-03|title=Topics Trending The TFP Office: #TimesUp, Hollywood Against Sexual Harassment ⋆ The Fashion Plate|url=https://thefashionplatemag.com/modern-culture/the-arts/film-tv/topics-trending-the-tfp-office-timesup-hollywood-against-sexual-harassment/|access-date=2020-06-04|website=The Fashion Plate|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Reese Witherspoon, Meryl Streep donate $500K to end sexual harassment in the workplace|url=https://boom997.com/news/3941455/reese-witherspoon-meryl-streep-donate-500k-to-end-sexual-harassment-in-the-workplace/|access-date=2020-06-04|website=boom 99.7|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180331072514/https://boom997.com/news/3941455/reese-witherspoon-meryl-streep-donate-500k-to-end-sexual-harassment-in-the-workplace/|archive-date=March 31, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>

Outside of her activism, Harrier is largely private, voicing her dislike for the [[paparazzi]] and is careful about what she puts on social media.<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":8" /><ref name=":7">{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=|title=Laura Harrier's Semaine|url=https://www.semaine.com/stories/-lauraharrier|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190831152313/https://www.semaine.com/stories/-lauraharrier|archive-date=August 31, 2019|access-date=2020-06-04|website=Semaine|language=en}}</ref> Harrier was in a relationship with American basketball player [[Klay Thompson]] from 2018 to early 2020.<ref name=":8">{{Cite web|last=Casely-Hayford|first=Alice|date=|title=Laura Harrier talks new show Hollywood, swapping red carpets for Zoom calls & the A-list friends helping her navigate fame|url=https://www.net-a-porter.com/porter/article-9fcb85a5caac7bea/cover-stories/cover-stories|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-06-01|website=Net-A-Porter}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=You May Recognize "Hollywood's" Laura Harrier from "One Life to Live"|url=https://www.oprahmag.com/entertainment/tv-movies/a32256951/who-is-laura-harrier-facts/|last=Janes|first=DeAnna|date=2020-05-01|website=[[Oprah Magazine]]|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200502034150/https://www.oprahmag.com/entertainment/tv-movies/a32256951/who-is-laura-harrier-facts/|archive-date=May 2, 2020|access-date=2020-05-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Mahjouri|first=Shakiel|date=2019-02-03|title=Laura Harrier Denies ‘Fake’ Engagement News|url=https://etcanada.com/news/414647/laura-harrier-denies-fake-engagement-news/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190204025936/https://etcanada.com/news/414647/laura-harrier-denies-fake-engagement-news/|archive-date=February 4, 2019|access-date=2020-06-04|website=[[ET Canada]]}}</ref>

